This paper is primarily focused on image instance retrieval, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also extensively uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly found in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses mathematical theories related to neural networks, which could potentially place it in the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on publicly available datasets, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
